<div class="[ home ]">
	<header>
		{%- rollup "src/input/js/eight-ball.js" | url -%}
		<div class="[ hero ]">
			<h1>
				<span class="[ text-fit ]">
					<span><span class="[ stroke ]" style="--thickness: 0.0125em; --fill-color: var(--accent-bg); --stroke-color: var(--accent-border);">Elly Loel</span></span>
					<span aria-hidden="true">Elly Loel</span>
				</span>
			</h1>
			<div class="[ flex flex-wrap gap-1 ]">
				<a href="https://en.pronouns.page/@ellyloel" class="[ link-icon-start text-decoration-none move-link-styling-to-child ]">{% inlineIcon "local:pronounspage", { "style": "vertical-align: middle" } %} <span class="[ p-pronouns ]"><span class="[ p-pronoun h-pronoun ]">she</span>/<span class="[ p-pronoun h-pronoun ]">her</span></span></a>
				<eight-ball>
					<span hidden>Design Engineer</span>
					<span hidden><a href="/blog/front-end-development-s-identity-crisis/">Front-end Developer?</a></span>
					<span hidden>Disenshittifier</span>
					<span hidden>Luddite</span>
					<span hidden>Web Designer</span>
					<span hidden>Accessibility specialist</span>
					<span hidden>Crip technoscientist</span>
					<button type="button" slot="action">{% labelledInlineIcon "fas:shuffle", { "aria-label": "Shuffle" } %}</button>
				</eight-ball>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="[ grid ]">
			<p class="[ h1 ]">
				<span class="[ detitlify ]">Hi, I’m <span class="[ logo-inline ]">{% labelledIcon "local:elly" %}</span></span>
				<eight-ball>
					<span hidden><span class="stroke">Web development is political</span>—every line of code shapes who has access, who’s excluded, and how power is distributed online.</span>
					<span hidden>Pushing back against the <span class="stroke">enshittification</span> of the web by building ethical, inclusive, and transparent tech.</span>
					<span hidden><span class="stroke">Queering the web</span> means designing inclusive, diverse spaces that challenge normative boundaries and embrace fluidity in both code and culture.</span>
					<span hidden>To be neutral on ableism perpetuates it—only by being <span class="stroke">anti-ableist</span> can you create accessible work.</span>
					<span hidden>In a continual battle against the status quo, we need <span class="stroke">progress over perfection</span>.</span>
					<span hidden>True web accessibility goes beyond standards, addressing the <span class="stroke">intersectionality</span> of barriers people face online.</span>
					<span hidden>Disability isn't defined by the individual; it's shaped by the barriers society creates & <span class="stroke">we are society</span>.</span>
					<span hidden><span class="stroke">Madding</span>, <span class="stroke">cripping</span>, and <span class="stroke">queering</span> will revolutionise the web—by reimagining accessibility as an ongoing, creative process rather than a set of fixed guidelines.</span>
					<span hidden><span class="stroke">Crip technoscience</span> empowers disabled people to reshape the world through critical design and activism, challenging ableist norms in technology and society.</span>
					<button type="button" slot="action">{% labelledInlineIcon "fas:shuffle", { "aria-label": "Shuffle" } %}</button>
				</eight-ball>
			</p>
			<div id="lego" class="[ lego-container ]">
				<is-land on:interaction="click,focusin">
					<template data-island>
						{%- rollup "src/input/js/model-viewer.js" | url -%}
						<script type="module">
							customElements
								.whenDefined("model-viewer")
								.then(() => {
									const modelViewer = document
										?.querySelector("model-viewer");
									modelViewer.onblur = function () {
										modelViewer.removeAttribute("tabindex");
									};
								});
						</script>
					</template>
					<model-viewer tabindex="0" loading="eager" alt="A 3D modeled Lego Minifigure designed to look like myself." src="/assets/3d/me.glb" camera-controls disable-pan disable-zoom shadow-intensity="0" exposure="0.75" shadow-softness="1" camera-orbit="31.49deg 78.9deg 98.24m" field-of-view="30deg">
						<img id="poster" src="/../assets/img/poster.webp" alt="A 3D modeled Lego Minifigure designed to look like myself." width="600" height="600">
						<div class="progress-bar" slot="progress-bar"></div>
					</model-viewer>
				</is-land>
			</div>
		</div>
	</header>

	<article class="[ about ][ flow ]">
		<div class="[ p-note ] [ flow ]">
			<p>I’m a <a href="/blog/front-end-development-s-identity-crisis/" class="[ p-role p-job-title ][ link-icon-start text-decoration-none move-link-styling-to-child ]">{% inlineIcon "local:UI" %} <span>Web Designer / Design Engineer</span></a> with a passion for <a href="/tags/accessibility/" class="[ link-icon-start text-decoration-none move-link-styling-to-child ]">{% inlineIcon "fas:universal-access" %} <span>Accessibility</span></a> and <a href="/tags/design-systems/" class="[ link-icon-start text-decoration-none move-link-styling-to-child ]">{% inlineIcon "fas:cubes" %} <span>Design Systems</span></a>, working to make the <a href="/tags/web/" class="[ link-icon-start text-decoration-none move-link-styling-to-child ]">{% inlineIcon "local:browser" %} <span>web</span></a> a more inclusive space in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melbourne#:~:text=%3A%20Narrm%20or-,Naarm,-%5B9%5D" class="[ p-locality ][ link-icon-start text-decoration-none move-link-styling-to-child ]">{% inlineIcon "fas:earth-oceania" %} <span>Naarm</span></a>.</p>
			<p>I love crafting with <a href="/tags/web-standards/" class="[ link-icon-start text-decoration-none move-link-styling-to-child ]">{% inlineIcon "fas:passport" %} <span>Web Standards</span></a> like <a href="/tags/html/" class="[ link-icon-start text-decoration-none move-link-styling-to-child ]">{% inlineIcon "local:code-rectangle" %} <span>HTML</span></a> & <a href="/tags/css/" class="[ link-icon-start text-decoration-none move-link-styling-to-child ]">{% inlineIcon "fab:css" %} <span>CSS</span></a>, and I’m always looking for ways to queer the web and make things less shit.</p>
			<p>I'm <a href="/garden/my-disabilities/" class="[ link-icon-start text-decoration-none move-link-styling-to-child ]">{% inlineIcon "fas:wheelchair-move" %} <span class="[ p-category ]">disabled</span></a> & {% inlineIcon "fas:brain" %} <span class="[ p-category ]">neurodivergent</span> & {% inlineIcon "fas:transgender" %} <span class="[ p-category ]">trans</span> & {% inlineIcon "fas:venus-double" %} <span class="[ p-category ]">queer</span>—this is where my work and identity meet.</p>
			<p>When I’m not advocating for better digital experiences, I’m probably geeking out over web standards or figuring out how to make life more equitable for {% inlineIcon "fas:users-between-lines" %} <strong>everyone</strong>.</p>
			<p>If you want, you can <a href="https://elly.to/ama" rel="me" class="[ u-url ][ link-icon-start text-decoration-none move-link-styling-to-child ]">{% inlineIcon "far:circle-question" %} <span>ask me anything</span></a>.</p>
			<p class="[ spotify-playing ]">The last song I listened to was <a href="https://www.last.fm/music/Never+Gonna+Give+You+Up/_/Rick+Astley" class="[ song ][ u-url ][ link-icon-start text-decoration-none move-link-styling-to-child ]">{% inlineIcon "fab:lastfm" %} "<span>Never Gonna Give You Up</span>"</a> by <em class="[ artist ]">Rick Astley</em>.</p>
		</div>
		<div hidden>
			<img class="[ u-photo u-logo ]" src="/../assets/img/pfp.jpg" alt='A digital drawing of me a white woman with blonde hair, smiling and doing a peace sign, wearing a white "golf le fleur" jumper.' loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="723" height="723">
			<div class="[ p-gender-identity ]">woman</div>
		</div>
		<aside class="[ flow ]">
			<h2>Where's Elly?</h2>
			{%- set disclosure = true -%}
			{%- include "social-links.njk" -%}
		</aside>
	</article>

	{%- include "crazy-filter.njk" -%}

	{%- feedBlock title = "Recent posts" -%}
	{%- set recentPosts = collections.postsSortedByDate | limit(10) -%}
	{%- for post in recentPosts -%}
		{%- set headingLevel = 3 -%}
		{%- set title = post.data.title -%}
		{%- set url = post.url -%}
		{%- setAsync "imageMarkup" -%}{%- endsetAsync -%}
		{%- if post.data.image -%}
			{%- setAsync "imageMarkup" -%}
			<svg viewBox="0 0 200 150" width="200" height="150">
				{%- set randomNumber -%}{%- random 0, 1 -%}{%- endset -%}
				<image class="image" xlink:href="https://res.cloudinary.com/ellyloel/image/fetch/f_auto/q_auto:low/c_fill,h_150,w_200/{{ post.data.image }}" x="-50%" y="-50%" width="200%" height="200%" filter="url(#filter)" opacity="0.65" style="transform: rotate({{ randomNumber | round(3) }}turn); transform-origin: center;"></image>
			</svg>
			{%- endsetAsync -%}
		{%- endif -%}
		{%- set date = post.data.date -%}
		{%- set label = "" -%}
		{%- if post.data.modified -%}
			{%- set label = "Last modified" -%}
		{%- elif post.data.created -%}
			{%- set label = "Created" -%}
		{%- endif -%}
		{%- set tags = post.data.tags -%}
		{%- include "feedItem.njk" -%}
	{%- endfor -%}
	{%- endfeedBlock -%}
</div>
